texts: 2020 tested us all – as individuals, communities, and as a company. The

throughout our society and world, including institutions of higher education.

text_str: At 2U, we combine a purpose-driven mission with a student-focused culture to increase access to high-quality education. We believe that more equitable access to high-quality education is the key to social mobility and economic security, that positive student outcomes have a resounding impact across all of civil society, and that diversity, equity, and inclusion beneﬁt everyone. We also believe in the importance of supporting each other, maintaining our culture, and giving back to our community.

helping our university partners deliver life-changing outcomes for their students
and having a positive impact on the world around us.

texts: We start this report with a look at our employees and culture, which are the foundational core of everything we do. Our employees are united by a single
mission—to eliminate the back row in higher education. And our shared passion for the mission unites us and deﬁnes our culture. As the COVID-19 pandemic drove
the need for social distancing protocols, we were able to pivot to an almost entirely remote work environment within a 48-hour period. Our employees’ response
has been inspiring. We supported each other as we worked together to support our university partners and students.

Our employees’ response has been inspiring. We supported each other as we worked together to support our university partners and students.

texts: 2U mandates privacy and security training for all new employees, as well as
annual training for all current employees. Our multidisciplinary approach to
continuous employee education reﬂects requirements of global regulatory
frameworks and data best practices. 2U’s privacy and security training covers
topics such as data security, FERPA, data protection, GDPR, and phishing.
text_str: 2U mandates privacy and security training for all new employees, as well as annual training for all current employees. Our multidisciplinary approach to continuous employee education reﬂects requirements of global regulatory frameworks and data best practices. 2U’s privacy and security training covers topics such as data security, FERPA, data protection, GDPR, and phishing.

texts: As part of this training, employees are required to read and acknowledge
policies that outline how 2U handles and protects personal and conﬁdential
information.  2U also conducts an annual campaign -- Cybersecurity and
Privacy Month -- to promote a culture of privacy and security at the company.
Moreover, our privacy and security teams regularly conduct role-based
training for employees across the business.

texts: In partnership with more than 30 top non-proﬁt universities, 2U
launched a $3 million Scholarship Fund designed to expand access
to critical tech training boot camps for historically underrepresented
candidates experiencing job loss or ﬁnancial hardship. Scholarships
of $2,500 each were made available to Black, Latino, and
Indigenous learners, as well as women, demonstrating both need
and merit, and can be applied to over 100 online tech boot camps.

texts: At 2U, data protection permeates every part of our business.  We understand the importance of safeguarding the data we
collect and process. We are constantly improving and iterating on our privacy and security programs to meet current best
practices and the requirements of changing regulatory regimes.
text_str: At 2U, data protection permeates every part of our business. We understand the importance of safeguarding the data we collect and process. We are constantly improving and iterating on our privacy and security programs to meet current best practices and the requirements of changing regulatory regimes.

texts: 2U’s Chief Privacy Oﬃcer leads our data privacy program, and our Senior Vice President, Cybersecurity oversees the
security program. Our privacy and security teams work together to develop policies, training, and educational initiatives
pertaining to data protection. The teams also partner on incident response, vendor management, and security/privacy
product control development.  Our data privacy and security programs are regularly reviewed by 2U’s internal audit team,
which also manages our annual SOC2 audit of security controls.
text_str: 2U’s Chief Privacy Oﬃcer leads our data privacy program, and our Senior Vice President, Cybersecurity oversees the security program. Our privacy and security teams work together to develop policies, training, and educational initiatives pertaining to data protection. The teams also partner on incident response, vendor management, and security/privacy product control development. Our data privacy and security programs are regularly reviewed by 2U’s internal audit team, which also manages our annual SOC2 audit of security controls.

texts: 2U’s privacy team implements privacy safeguards and controls to ensure the safe and secure use of personal information.
We adapt and update our privacy program to align with changing regulatory requirements, such as the General Data
Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and South Africa’s Protection of Personal
Information Act (POPIA).  Our privacy program embeds privacy-by-design into the product development and data lifecycle
and focuses on transparency, data collection and data use controls.
text_str: 2U’s privacy team implements privacy safeguards and controls to ensure the safe and secure use of personal information. We adapt and update our privacy program to align with changing regulatory requirements, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and South Africa’s Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA). Our privacy program embeds privacy-by-design into the product development and data lifecycle and focuses on transparency, data collection and data use controls.

texts: 2U implements robust security safeguards to protect information, such as anomaly and behavior-based detection of
suspicious security related activity, multi-factor authentication, least privileged access rights, endpoint security, vulnerability
and patch management policies and processes, and continuous penetration testing. We conduct quarterly assessments to
ensure 2U's compliance with Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard.
